        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 11:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1117 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Salisbury, or near Rockwell, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Salisbury, Granite Quarry, Rockwell, Faith, High Rock Lake, and Gold
Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
